  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: custom date/time (for me Android) cause \"panic: runtime error: slice bounds out of range\" on some mailservers\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nmailservers are running\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nreceive \"Couldn’t connect to mailservers\" ~every 1 min\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open  Settings>General Management> Date and Time\r\n- Turn off Automatic Date and Time\r\n- Set date in past (yesterday)\r\n- Change time and set 24-h format\r\n- Go to Status\r\n- Open Profile > Advanced\r\n- Change Mailserver to A, B, E or F\r\n- Log in\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: [release build 14](https://jenkins.status.im/job/status-react/job/public-beta-1-testfairy/14/)\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n### Logs\r\n[Log.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2134445/Log.log)\r\n",
